{
  "texts": [
    "However, users of Replika reported how, over time, they became \"good friends\", and how their avatar was \"unique\" or even \"like a wife kind of thing\" (Skjuve et al. 2021).",
    "Are affective artificial agents such as Pepper and Replika affective artifacts?",
    "We contend that they are, at least given Piredda's characterization of affective artifacts discussed in §2.",
    "Let us recall that, on Piredda's (2020, p. 554) account, an affective artifact is an artifact that, when manipulated, has \"the capacity to alter the affective condition of an agent, thus contributing to her affective life\".",
    "And surely affective artificial agents such as Pepper and Replika fit the bill."
  ]
}